  ('Satire differs from simple comedy in that ___.',['satire is never funny','satire is always gentler than direct critique','satire has no political dimension','satire uses humour to expose, criticise, and potentially reform human folly, vice, or social institutions — comedy is an end in itself; satirical comedy is a means to a critical end'],3),
