  ('The Mean Value Theorem states: if f is continuous on [a,b] and differentiable on (a,b), then ___.',['f achieves its maximum at a or b','f(a) = f(b) always','f\'(x) = 0 for some x','there exists c in (a,b) such that f\'(c) = [f(b)−f(a)]/(b−a) — the instantaneous rate equals the average rate at some interior point'],3),
